        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000045"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A DNA segment essential for the initiation of transcription at a defined location in a DNA molecule, although this location might not be one single base, and it is recognized by a specific Eσ. A promoter guides transcription initiation in only one direction, with directionality determined by the strand on which its associated transcription start site resides.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:comment>Promoter coordinates are calculated based on the most upstream TSS. The left coordinate is 60 bases upstream and the right coordinate is 20 bases downstream the TSS.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">promoter</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


