                    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000009"/>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000173"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000002"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </owl:equivalentClass>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>a TFBS that is involved in transcription regulation</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:OBAGER_0000033>TFRS</obo:OBAGER_0000033>
        <rdfs:comment>The definition of transcription factor requires that these bound &quot;near&quot; the promoter. This is clearly a site property, but we have to define the meaning of &quot;near&quot; and/or of the complex TF bound to TFRS.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>Transcription factor regulatory sites (TFRSs) directly regulate promoter activity, but observations of increased or decreased expression of a DNA segment also provide evidence of the regulatory activity of the site.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transcription factor regulatory site</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000035 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000035">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000185"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000039"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000095"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000180"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000002"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A DNA continuous segment that carries the information for the structure of at least one functional RNA or polypeptide chain. If a gene carries information for more than one simple product, it implies overlapping coding sequences or overlapping functional RNA-bearing regions.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:comment>The definition is intended to include genes that produce more than one product, e. g. dnaX produces by frameshifting both subunit tau and subunit gamma of the DNA polymerase.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>The definition is intended to regard independent cistrons that code for subunits of heteromultimeric proteins as different genes. For example, the cistrons that code for subunits of IHF, ihfA and ihfB, are differente genes.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">functional gene</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


