    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000088">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000083"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>a trans-acting regulator of transcription that regulates the extension of the RNA molecule after promoter clearance</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>Adapted from GO:0006354</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">trans-acting regulator of transcription elongation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000089 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000089">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000083"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>A trans-acting regulator of transcription initiation that regulates the dissociation of the RNA–DNA hybrid and the release of RNA polymerase from its DNA template.</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>Adapted from GO:0006353</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">trans-acting regulator of transcription termination</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000092 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000092">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000176"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000137"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A material entity that consists of two or more atoms that are all connected via covalent bonds such that any atom can be transitively connected with any other atom.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>COB
COB_0000013</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">molecular entity</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000093 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000093">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000092"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A molecular entity that is not directly carried nor encoded in the genome.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">small molecule</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000094 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000094">
        <owl:equivalentClass>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000073"/>
                        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000074"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                    <owl:Restriction>
                        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000175"/>
                        <owl:qualifiedCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">1</owl:qualifiedCardinality>
                        <owl:onClass rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000011"/>
                    </owl:Restriction>
                </owl:intersectionOf>
            </owl:Class>
        </owl:equivalentClass>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000045"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000185"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A set of adjacent genes whose transcription is coordinated by one or several mutually overlapping transcription units that are transcribed in the same direction and share at least one gene.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID: ﻿32665585</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:comment>On the RegulonDB website, the operon region begins at the most upstream regulatory site and ends at the transcription termination site of the last transcription unit (TU), and includes internal TFRSs and promoters. Thus, operon regions summarize all available information for maximal sets of overlapping TUs.

However, from an ontological perspective, regulatory properties cannot be treated as transitive. In particular, we cannot infer that if a transcription factor (TF) bound to a TFRS regulates a TU, then it also regulates the operon to which that TU belongs. This is because, for example, in an operon with genes ABC composed of two TUs (AB and BC), the regulatory properties of the BC TU do not necessarily hold for the AB TU.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>The fact that the genes of an operon are coordinated by transcription units is represented in the axiom gene &apos;is part of&apos; some &apos;transcription unit&apos;. To calculate the operon, we have to find the TUs that overlap, but I think this is outside the capabilites of OWL. So we should assert the relation operon &apos;has part&apos; some &apos;transcription unit&apos;.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">operon</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000095 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000095">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000049"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A continuous RNA segment that carries the information for the structure of at least one functional RNA or polypeptide chain. If a gene carries information for more than one product, it is composed of overlapping CDSs or functional RNA-bearing regions.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transcribed region of a gene</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000096 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000096">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000071"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A genetically specified biomacromolecular entity that is part of a polymeric chain.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">genetically specified biomacromolecular segment</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000097 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000097">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000071"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A biomacromolecular entity that consists of one or more complete polymeric chains.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">genetically specified biomacromolecule</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000098 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000098">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000097"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A biomacromolecule that consists of ribonucleotides.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">RNA molecule</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000099 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000099">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000097"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A biomacromolecule that consists of desoxyribonucleotides.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">DNA molecule</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000100 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000100">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000095"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000046"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000013"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>an RNA segment that carries the information for at least one functional RNA</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transcribed region of RNA gene</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000101 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000101">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000098"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An RNA molecule that carries at least one transcribed coding segment.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:OBAGER_0000033>mRNA</obo:OBAGER_0000033>
        <rdfs:comment>some mRNAs have their ends processed, so not all of them can be regarded as primary transcripts nor as mature transcripts [PMID: ﻿2992951, 2433046]</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">messenger RNA</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000102 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000102">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000101"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>An mRNA that lacks a 5′ UTR or leader region.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:IAO_0000119>PMID:33349119</obo:IAO_0000119>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">leaderless mRNA</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000103 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBAGER_0000103">
